Key Aspects of LangGraph with Meanings
| Aspect                  | Meaning                                                                                                  |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| State Management        | Stores shared data that moves through the workflow. Each node can read or update this state.             |
| Nodes                   | Individual functions or processing steps in the graph. A node performs a specific task.                  |
| Edges                   | Connections between nodes that define workflow direction. They control how execution moves.              |
| Conditional Routing     | Dynamically selects the next step based on conditions or outputs. Helps create intelligent workflows.    |
| Cycles / Loops          | Allows workflows to repeat steps until a condition is satisfied. Useful for retries and reasoning loops. |
| Tool Calling            | Enables agents to use external tools like APIs, databases, or search systems.                            |
| Memory                  | Stores past interactions or workflow history. Helps maintain context in conversations.                   |
| Adaptability            | Allows the system to change behavior based on inputs, results, or situations.                            |
| Reasoning               | Helps agents think step-by-step before generating answers or actions.                                    |
| Planning                | Decides the sequence of actions needed to complete a task effectively.                                   |
| Reflection              | Lets the agent review and improve its own output before finalizing.                                      |
| Retry Mechanism         | Automatically retries failed operations to improve reliability.                                          |
| Error Handling          | Detects and manages failures gracefully without crashing the workflow.                                   |
| Multi-Agent Systems     | Multiple specialized agents collaborate together to solve tasks.                                         |
| Human-in-the-Loop       | Allows humans to review, approve, or guide workflow execution.                                           |
| Persistence             | Saves workflow progress so it can continue later without losing state.                                   |
| Checkpointing           | Creates save points during execution for recovery or resuming.                                           |
| Streaming               | Sends outputs gradually in real time instead of waiting for full completion.                             |
| Parallel Execution      | Runs multiple tasks simultaneously to improve speed and efficiency.                                      |
| Workflow Orchestration  | Coordinates multiple workflow steps and manages overall execution flow.                                  |
| Graph Architecture      | Represents workflows as connected graphs rather than fixed linear chains.                                |
| Context Awareness       | Uses surrounding information and previous interactions intelligently.                                    |
| Decision Making         | Chooses actions dynamically based on current state and conditions.                                       |
| Task Delegation         | Assigns subtasks to specialized agents or tools automatically.                                           |
| Modularity              | Breaks workflows into reusable independent components.                                                   |
| Scalability             | Supports expansion to larger and more complex AI systems.                                                |
| Observability           | Helps monitor workflow execution, states, and debugging information.                                     |
| Extensibility           | Makes it easy to add new tools, nodes, or workflow logic.                                                |
| Autonomous Execution    | Allows agents to complete tasks independently with minimal human input.                                  |
| Event-Driven Execution  | Triggers actions automatically when certain events occur.                                                |
| Dynamic Workflowing     | Changes execution paths dynamically during runtime.                                                      |
| Interrupt Handling      | Supports pausing and resuming workflows safely.                                                          |
| RAG Integration         | Combines retrieval systems with LLMs for knowledge-based answering.                                      |
| Conversation Management | Handles multi-turn conversations while preserving context.                                               |
| State Persistence       | Maintains workflow state across sessions or executions.                                                  |
| Async Execution         | Supports non-blocking concurrent operations for better performance.                                      |
| Agent Coordination      | Manages communication and cooperation between multiple agents.                                           |
| Fallback Strategies     | Switches to backup methods if primary execution fails.                                                   |
| Validation              | Verifies correctness of outputs before proceeding further.                                               |
| Execution Control       | Manages workflow start, stop, transitions, and execution flow.                                           |
| Reusability             | Allows workflow components to be reused in different projects.                                           |
| Explainability          | Makes workflow decisions and execution easier to understand.                                             |
| Integration Capability  | Connects with APIs, databases, vector stores, and external services.                                     |
| Production Readiness    | Supports stable and reliable deployment in real-world applications.                                      |
| Custom Logic Support    | Allows developers to define their own workflow behaviors and rules.                                      |
| Stateful Conversations  | Maintains intelligent long-running conversations with memory.                                            |
